Class GenericList<T extends Searchable<T>>

java.lang.Object
cop3330.util.GenericList<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of elements stored in the list, which must implement Searchable for type T
public class GenericList<T extends Searchable<T>> extends Object
A generic list class that stores objects implementing the Searchable interface.

This class provides basic list functionalities such as adding elements, retrieving by index, checking the size, and sorting. It prevents duplicate entries by checking for existing elements before adding and dynamically resizes the internal storage array as needed.

Internally, elements are stored in an Object[] array for generic compatibility. Elements are cast to type T upon retrieval or processing.

  • Method Details

    • add

      public void add(T obj)
      Adds a new element to the list if it is not already present.

      This method throws IllegalArgumentException if the element does not implement Searchable. If the internal array capacity is exceeded, the list automatically grows. Duplicate elements (determined by Searchable.isEqual(Object)) are not added.

      Parameters:
      obj - the element to add
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if obj does not implement Searchable

    • get

      public T get(int index)
      Retrieves the element at the specified index.
      Parameters:
      index - the zero-based index of the element to retrieve
      Returns:
      the element at the specified index
      Throws:
      ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is out of range (index < 0 || index >= size)

    • size

      public int size()
      Returns the number of elements currently stored in the list.
      Returns:
      the current size of the list

    • growList

      private void growList()
      Doubles the capacity of the internal array and copies over existing elements. This method is called automatically when the list capacity is exceeded.

    • findMatch

      public T findMatch(String key)
      Finds and returns the first element in the list that matches the given key.

      Matching is determined by the Searchable.isMatch(String) method.

      Parameters:
      key - the search key used to find a matching element
      Returns:
      the first matching element, or null if no match is found

    • query

      public GenericList<T> query(String key)
      Returns a new GenericList containing all elements that match the given key.

      Matching is determined by the Searchable.isMatch(String) method.

      Parameters:
      key - the search key used to find matching elements
      Returns:
      a GenericList containing all matching elements; may be empty if no matches found

    • contains

      public boolean contains(T obj)
      Determines whether the specified element exists in the list.

      Equality is determined by the Searchable.isEqual(Object) method.

      Parameters:
      obj - the element to check for containment
      Returns:
      true if the element exists in the list; false otherwise

    • sort

      public void sort()
      Sorts the elements in the list in ascending order according to their natural ordering.

      This method uses Arrays.sort(Object[], int, int) to sort the internal array from index 0 (inclusive) to size (exclusive).

      All elements must implement Comparable and be mutually comparable, otherwise a ClassCastException will be thrown at runtime.

      Throws:
      ClassCastException - if elements are not mutually comparable
